Snake Game Made By Omkar Hadawale

🐍 Classic Snake Game in Python

A modern recreation of the nostalgic, arcade-style Snake game built from scratch using Python and Pygame in the PyCharm IDE.

This project demonstrates core game development concepts including event handling, collision detection, real-time score tracking, and game loop optimization.

Features
Smooth Controls: Grid-based movement using the arrow keys (or WASD).

Dynamic Growth: The snake grows longer and speeds up slightly every time it eats an apple.

Collision Detection: Game over triggers if the snake hits the screen boundaries or crashes into its own tail.

Live Scoreboard: Real-time score tracking displayed right on the screen.

Clean UI: Simple, retro-inspired graphics with a restart option.



